        "class": "",
        "text": " rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the burning heat of hunger.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hariri, the humoristic author of the cycle of stories in rhymed Arabic prose and verse, called 'Makamat,' puts into the mouth of his ne'er do well Abu Seid very similar words to describe a famished man - ",
        "children": []
      },
